          },
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\nReport: `docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\nFinding: #24\n\nMoved from mistakenly filed meta issue: ConcaveTrillion/ocr-container-meta#317\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `pyproject.toml:114`\n- `scripts/coverage_reporter.py:9`\n- `README.md:117`\n\nThe real coverage gate is 87%, but the reporter and README state 80%.\n\nImpact:\n\n- Contributors get incorrect guidance about CI failures.\n\nRemediation:\n\n- Make the reporter read `tool.coverage.report.fail_under` from `pyproject.toml`.\n- Update README and tests.\n\n---\nThis issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
